On 14 May 2011 at 17:13, Chris DuBois wrote:
| Thanks Dirk. ?Quick newbie followup question: Can we put functions within the
| inline C++ code? ?The following doesn't compile, for example:
| src <- '
| int addition (int a, int b)
| {
| ??int r;
| ??r=a+b;
| ??return (r);
